{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/stick-your-notes-on-any-site","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"6648c1dd-2143-598a-a481-2493434886c7","html":"<p><code class=\"language-text\">Sticky Notes</code> is a browser extension that helps in taking notes for a site, that too on the site itself. The notes persists for future use and can be used to chalk down notes or important points for that page/site. These drag-able notes can be placed anywhere on the page, where ever it may be relevant. You can create notes via context menu or using shortcut keys. Usage guide is mentioned in the extension page.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">Sticky Notes</code> by Hiroki Kumamoto is available as <a href=\"https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/stickynotes/imcecnigpdchlakcljkjjhddmilnmcji\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Chrome Extension</a> and <a href=\"https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/sticky-notes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Firefox Addon</a> .</p>\n<p>I use it to chalk down action items from PRDs, Design specification, etc that I have to work upon. It is really helpful on github pages to note points for that repository like configuration option, current version which I am using for update purpose, pull-request/issue notes, or common usage cli command. I usually end up forgetting cli options for various tools, like <a href=\"https://github.com/ytdl-org/youtube-dl\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">youtube-dl</a>, and pin frequent cli commands for them on the web.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/828bd/sticky-notes.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 57.08333333333333%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/8ac56/sticky-notes.webp 240w,\n/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/d3be9/sticky-notes.webp 480w,\n/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/e46b2/sticky-notes.webp 960w,\n/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/f992d/sticky-notes.webp 1440w,\n/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/882b9/sticky-notes.webp 1920w,\n/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/ad234/sticky-notes.webp 2310w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/8ff5a/sticky-notes.png 240w,\n/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/e85cb/sticky-notes.png 480w,\n/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/d9199/sticky-notes.png 960w,\n/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/07a9c/sticky-notes.png 1440w,\n/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/29114/sticky-notes.png 1920w,\n/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/828bd/sticky-notes.png 2310w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/b60ba94e9af312ec17cc5bcf660478b3/d9199/sticky-notes.png\"\n          alt=\"Screenshot\"\n          title=\"Screenshot\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Official Site: <a href=\"https://blog.kumabook.tokyo/stickynotes/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Sticky Notes</a></p>\n<hr>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/stick-your-notes-on-any-site","tagSlugs":["/tag/tools/","/tag/browser/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2019-04-11T18:05:00.738Z","description":"Take your own notes for a page of a site or anywhere on the web via Firefox Addon. The notes persist for that site for future use. ","tags":["Tools","Browser"],"title":"Stick your notes on any site","socialImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/stick-your-notes-on-any-site"}}}